Reasoning: The paper discusses a methodology based on bibliometric data for selecting the best products of a laboratory, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a decision support system for research organizations. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories as the paper discusses the use of bibliometric data for evaluation. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper discusses the limitations of the peer review approach and proposes a quantitative methodology for evaluation.
